title._content: Milo Maltbie, E.E. McCall, Wm. Hayward  (LOC)

description._content: Bain News Service,, publisher. Milo Maltbie, E.E. McCall, Wm. Hayward [between ca. 1910 and ca. 1915] 1 negative : glass ; 5 x 7 in. or smaller. Notes: Title from data provided by the Bain News Service on the negative. Photograph shows Edward Everett McCall, Chairman of the New York State Public Service Commission, Milo R. Maltbe, Commissioner of the New York State Public Service Commission and William Hayward who served as Commissioner of the New York State Public Service Commission in 1915. (Source: Flickr Commons project, 2012) Forms part of: George Grantham Bain Collection (Library of Congress). Format: Glass negatives. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print General information about the Bain Collection is available at hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.ggbain Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ggbain.18796 Call Number: LC-B2- 3430-8

note._content: foot is wrapped.  NYT article notes his ankle was injured in April, 1915.
